Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.22,0:00:03.65,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Today I took a walk with Takeshi-san along the Charles River.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.12,0:00:08.07,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I reflected on the four years that I’ve spent here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.64,0:00:12.94,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,At first I was elated, but things were tough until I met Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.56,0:00:17.05,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I think I’ve changed a lot since I met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.29,0:00:22.61,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I suppose it wasn’t time for romance, but being alone was a downer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.93,0:00:26.94,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,When you feel down you want someone to be around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.88,0:00:32.56,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,But it doesn’t mean that you ought to seek out a boyfriend thoughtlessly just because you’re feeling sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.62,0:00:35.98,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I’ve gotten my feelings hurt a few times that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.02,0:00:40.32,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,But Takeshi-san is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.67,0:00:43.76,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I feel safe just being with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.85,0:00:47.23,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I think it’s the first time I’ve felt this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.59,0:00:53.41,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,Next year, Takeshi-san will return to Japan and start working at a research center.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:00:56.72,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,What will happen to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.60,0:01:01.64,Default,Touko,0,0,0,,I would love to work in the same research center as Takeshi-san.
